    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-03T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-03T14:00:00-05:00" n="427"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/1454: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-03T16:00:00-03:00"
                            >October 3, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 3—4 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>346. Embassy’s despatch 1768, September 18.<note n="67" xml:id="d427fn67">Not
                        printed.</note> The Director of the Exchange informs me that Bank of Brazil
                    will resume the allocation of dollar exchange for remittance of earnings and
                    administrative expenses of some foreign (predominantly American) companies
                    operating in Brazil.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
